videos.description: TCU's Kenrich Williams slams one home off the inbounds pass from Alex Robinson.
videos.headline: Williams throws down off inbound pass

videos.description: TCU's Kouat Noi sinks third 3-pointer to get the home crowd riled up.
videos.headline: Noi is hot from 3-point line

videos.description: Sagaba Konate makes huge block for West Virginia and Teddy Allen draws the three-point play with an and-1 on the breakaway.
videos.headline: WVU bounces back with huge block plus and-1

videos.description: TCU's Vladimir Brodziansky sends a bounce pass to Kouat Noi in the paint who slams it home.
videos.headline: Noi throws down two-handed slam

videos.description: Vladimir Brodziansky stuffs Jevon Carter on full-court drive to the hoop.
videos.headline: Brodziansky denies Carter on coast-to-coast drive

videos.description: Alex Robinson hits a buzzer-beater from just over half court but unfortunately did not get it off in time.
videos.headline: Robinson's buzzer-beater is called back

videos.description: Desmond Bane tops off TCU's 12-1 run with a 3-pointer to extend the Horned Frog's lead.
videos.headline: Bane drains crucial 3

videos.description: Kouat Noi gets ejected from the game for overreacting and shoving Lamont West to the ground after he grabs his hand on transition.
videos.headline: TCU's Noi is tossed for shoving West to the ground

videos.description: Jamie Dixon is all smiles after defeating No. 7 West Virginia 82-73 for the first time in school history.
videos.headline: Dixon after upsetting West Virginia: 'I'm happy for the fans'

videos.description: TCU's leading scorer Alex Robinson discusses how they prepared this week to defeat No. 7 West Virginia 82-73.
videos.headline: Robinson: 'We knew we needed to step up our defense'
